data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Shift modifier used on Alt+C knocks additional 30% off width, on Alt+P knocks addtional 10% off height and uses alternative 3:4 aspect ratio and on Alt+T knocks additional 25% off height and uses alternative 3:2 aspect ratio.

data.name: linkLabel2.Text
data.value: To enable win[dows] key on right side of keyboard in lieu of rarely used one, e.g. context menu key on microsoft keyboards and print screen on lenovo x1 carbon/yoga devices, see SharpKeys. A windows keyboard shortcut that is useful in conjunction with the ones above is Win+Home that will minimize all windows except the currently active one. If you want to enable this app to automatically start when you signin see win+r | shell:appsfolder for context menu allowing creation of shortcut that you can then place in %appdata%\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu\Programs\Startup folder [ todo: provide a "Start app at Sign In" setting ].
